HEADWORD: Cautelous
<hw>Cau"te*lous</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[F.
<ets>cauteleux</ets>, LL. <ets>cautelosus</ets>. See
<er>Cautel</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Caution; prudent; wary.</def>
<mark>[Obs.]</mark> ⟦ldquo⟧<xex>Cautelous</xex>, though young.⟦rdquo⟧
<rj><au>Drayton.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Crafty; deceitful; false.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark>
<rj><au>Shak.</au></rj></p>

<p>-- <wordforms><wf>Cau"te*lous*ly</wf>, <pos>adv.</pos> --
<wf>Cau"te*lous*ness</wf>, <pos>n.</pos>
<mark>[Obs.]</mark></wordforms>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Cauter</ent>⟦br⟧
